{
  "text": "The secondary outcomes were the visual analog scale pain scores for both back and leg systems (VAS-BP, VAS-LP) and the Oswestry Disability Index (ODI), both have been used frequently in studies involving patients with lumbar spinal stenosis on a scale of 0 to100 [CITATION_1] . All patients were blind to the roles of pain scores and ODI.",
